From the DVD description:

&quot;The Book of Mormon Movie is the incredible true story of Nephi and his family as they leave the city of Jerusalem in 600 BC, cross the Arabian desert, build a ship and sail to the &quot;Promised Land&quot; in the Americas. Nephi's journey is full of danger, mystery, intrigue and romance.

With high adventure, sweeping music and breathtaking cinematography, The Book of Mormon Movie Volume 1: The Journey will captivate and inspire. Its message of faith is just as timely now as it was 2600 years ago.&quot;

-------------------------

To call it a &quot;true&quot; story is a bit of a stretch, to say the least, but I guess it's no more or less true than, say The Ten Commandments. Oh, and this is &quot;Volume 1&quot;, although no sequels were made. According to BoxOfficeMojo, the budget was $1,5 million and it grossed about $1,68 million in the US. It was widely panned by the critics that even bothered reviewing it.

Directed by Gary Rogers. Written by Craig Clyde and Gary Rogers. Starring Noah Danby, Bryce Chamberlain, Jacque Gray, Jan Broberg, Mark Gollaher, Cragun Foulger, Michael Flynn, and others.

